    "description": "Protolife: Other Side - is arcade game which can also be called as &quot;reverse tower defense&quot;. You have to lead squads of alien creatures though the ever-growing defense line on miltiple locations. The more creatures you save the easier it will be to reach the main goal: find the interplanet transport and evacuate.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Plot</h2>One year passed since Protolife game events. Mankind started colonization of new planet. It was called Planet of Leonov (aka Leo-Nóva). The alien biotechnologies was found on this planet too. But this time the alien core was found and blasted with orbital strike, avoiding heavy ground combat.<br>Alien overseer who also acts as backup core decides to evaculate survived creatures from planet. He's scared. Scared not of humans.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Features</h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li> 5 species of creatures with own abilities<br></li><li> 4 common abilities<br></li><li> 6 zones with different level architecture<br></li><li> partially destructible landscape<br></li><li> familiar towers and buildings from original Protolife (as enemies this time)<br></li><li> new towers and buildings<br></li><li> each level must be beaten several times in order to evacuate as much creatures as possible. Each attempt is harder than the previous one.<br></li><li> special missions which affect the other levels</li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Controls</h2>Keyboard, keyboard+mouse or gamepad. You directly control leader's movement, other creature follow the leader. Also you may activate one of the abilities for the whole squad.",
